definitions.definition: Any mollusc, of the class Cephalopoda, which includes squid, cuttlefish, octopus, nautiloids etc.
An apple brandy made in Normandy, France.
A glass of this spirit.

An organic molecule in which a nitrogenous heterocyclic base (or nucleobase), which can be either a double-ringed purine or a single-ringed pyrimidine, is covalently attached to a five-carbon pentose sugar (deoxyribose in DNA or ribose in RNA). When the phosphate group is covalently attached to the pentose sugar, it forms a nucleotide.
The quality of being different or distinct.
The result or product of being different or distinct.
Anything made wholly or largely of iron, especially when used for decoration.
An ironworks.
A factory in which iron is manufactured or iron goods are made
A designated player that attempts to prevent the opposing team from scoring by protecting a goal.
To enlarge; to make bigger.
definitions.example: The eye doctor put drops in my eye to dilate the pupil so he could see the nerve better.

definitions.definition: To become wider or larger; to expand.
definitions.example: His heart dilates and glories in his strength.

definitions.definition: To speak largely and copiously; to dwell in narration; to enlarge; with "on" or "upon".
To use a dilator to widen (something, such as a vagina).
(dismissal, 4chan) Expression of anger and contempt, specifically at transgender women.
Any of several unrelated fish.
An upstart.
An elaterid; a click beetle.
A shallow sailboat with a rectilinear or V-shaped cross section.
To extend from, above or beyond a surface or boundary; to bulge outward; to stick out.
To cause to extend from a surface or boundary; to cause to stick out.
To thrust forward; to drive or force along.
To dissociate atoms or molecules into electrically charged species; to be thus dissociated.
Capable of producing ions.
(grammar) The plural number.
(grammar) A word in the form in which it potentially refers to something other than one person or thing; and other than two things if the language has a dual form.
Lacking certification or official documentation
Not officially registered
A comb, required to be worn at all times by Sikhs, one of the five Ks.
A colourful printed cotton garment worn by women in East Africa.
Of or pertaining to psychotherapeutics (psychotherapy)
Cathartic
In a skillful manner; with skill.
Any protein containing bound phosphate
A person who favors the abolition of any particular institution or practice.
A person who favored or advocated the abolition of slavery.
To program something in advance.
To predispose to certain thoughts or behaviours.
definitions.example: hard-wired behavior, or behavior that a dog's genetics have preprogrammed him to do

definitions.definition: To make hot and rosy, as with drinking.
(by extension) To confuse; befuddle; throw into panic by making overwrought with confusion.
definitions.example: He seemed to get flustered when speaking in front of too many people.

definitions.definition: To be in a heat or bustle; to be agitated and confused.
Confused, befuddled, in a state of panic by having become overwrought with confusion.
definitions.example: The speaker became quite flustered when she dropped all her notes.

definitions.definition: Any chemical reaction in which a compound is decomposed after absorbing a photon
Being or relating to a division of a traditionally male sport that is reserved for females.
A type of spacecraft capable of traveling to the solar systems of other stars
To give up; yield to another.
definitions.example: Edward decided to cede the province.

definitions.definition: To give way.
A carriage pulled by two or more draught animals (generally draught horses) harnessed one behind the other, both providing the pulling power but only the animal in front able to steer.
(transferred sense) A bicycle or tricycle in which two people sit one behind the other, both able to pedal but only the person in front able to steer.
A group of two or more people, machines etc. working together; close collaboration.
To move backwards to an earlier stage; to devolve.
To move from east to west.
To perform a regression on an explanatory variable.
definitions.example: When we regress Y on X, we use the values of variable X to predict those of Y.

definitions.definition: That has been subject to regression
A young woman or girl.
definitions.example: Come and dance, ye lads and lasses!

definitions.definition: (Mackem) A sweetheart.
A Chinese martial art.
Of or relating to epigenesis.
Of or relating to epigenetics.
The halogenated hydrocarbon 2-bromo-2-chloro-1,1,1-trifluoroethane that is used as an inhalational general anaesthetic
The size or shape of a person's body.
The waist or bodice of a woman's dress.
A small bouquet of flowers, originally worn attached to the bodice of a woman's dress.
